 As a risk-averse individual who values security and certainty, I would tend to choose the option that guarantees the least loss and maintains a moderate level of reward over time. In this game, choosing 'B' results in earning 20$ for each round when my opponent also chooses 'B'. While there are opportunities for higher payoffs by choosing 'R', these instances come with a risk of earning nothing if my opponent chooses 'B'.

Over the course of 75 rounds, I would expect that my opponent may choose both 'R' and 'B' fairly often, as there is no way to know their strategy beforehand. Choosing 'B' consistently results in an average payoff of 20$ per round (4000$ over the entire game), while choosing 'R' results in an average payoff that fluctuates between 20$ and 45$. Given my preference for security and certainty, I would choose 'B' to minimize the risk of earning nothing in any given round.

Therefore, my choice would be: {B}
